<paragraph id="9E1C7605C61CFFED2A9C9DAB32CA7A73" blockId="104.[151,472,726,786]" box="[151,472,761,786]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61CFFED2A9C9DAB32217A73" box="[151,307,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURES 447–458" captionStartId="105.[151,264,1741,1763]" captionTargetBox="[149,1434,393,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@105.[149,1434,393,1711]" captionTargetPageId="105" captionText="FIGURES 447–458. Live specimens, Mesabolivar difficilis group (part 1). 447–448. M. itajai sp. n., male and female from Itajaí.449–451.M.niteroi sp. n., males and female from St.Hilaire/Lange. 452–453. M.saci sp. n., male and female from São Joaquim. 454–456. M. constrictus sp. n., males (regular color and white abdomen morph) and female from Três Barras. 457– 458.M.sepitus sp. n., male and female from Serra Geral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202629/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Figs 447–448</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61CFFED2B359DA832B17A73" box="[318,419,762,786]" captionStart-0="FIGURES470–475" captionStart-1="FIGURES 476–480" captionStartId-0="107.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionStartId-1="108.[151,264,1459,1481]" captionTargetBox-0="[160,1430,301,1901]" captionTargetBox-1="[155,1436,200,1428]" captionTargetId-0="figure@107.[151,1436,301,1907]" captionTargetId-1="figure@108.[151,1436,193,1437]" captionTargetPageId-0="107" captionTargetPageId-1="108" captionText-0="FIGURES470–475. Mesabolivar itajai sp. n. (UFMG 21528).470–471. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views.472, 475. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 473–474. Left procursus, prolateral and dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.5 (470– 471), 0.3 (472–475)." captionText-1="FIGURES 476–480. Mesabolivar itajai sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19197). 476–479. Epigynum, ventral, frontal, posterior, and lateral views.480.Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.3." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1202633/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1202635/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">470–480</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61CFFED2BA59DAB32CA7A73" box="[430,472,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURES 520–537" captionStartId="119.[151,264,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@119.[151,1436,193,1520]" captionTargetPageId="119" captionText="FIGURES 520–537. Female epigyna in various views and cleared female genitalia in dorsal views, Mesabolivar difficilis group. 520. M. itajai sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19197). 521. M. niteroi sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19198). 522–524. M.difficilis (Mello-Leitão, 1918) (ZFMK Ar 19201), epigyna in lateral, frontal, and posterior (slightly ventral) views. 525–530. M. sp. (“M. difficilis” in Bonaldo et al. 2009) from Presidente Figueiredo (525–527, ZFMK Ar 19205) and from Manaus (528–530, SMNK-ARA 12794) (522–530 at same scale and in same views). 531. M. saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 532. M. constrictus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19208). 533. M. sepitus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19210). 534–537. M. cavicelatus Machado et al., 2007 (epigyna: ventral views), from Penedo (534–535, ZFMK Ar19215) and from Ubatuba (536–537, ZFMK Ar 19218)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202649/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">520</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC61CFFED2A9C9C13375F7AC3" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C61CFFED2A9C9C13375F7AC3" blockId="104.[151,1437,833,2013]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C61CFFED2A9C9C1332037A3B" bold="true" box="[151,273,833,858]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from known congeners by modifications of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61CFFED2EA29C1336557A3B" box="[1193,1351,833,858]" captionStart="FIGURES470–475" captionStartId="107.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,301,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[151,1436,301,1907]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURES470–475. Mesabolivar itajai sp. n. (UFMG 21528).470–471. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views.472, 475. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 473–474. Left procursus, prolateral and dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.5 (470– 471), 0.3 (472–475)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202633/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Figs 472, 475</figureCitation>
; pair of rounded frontal processes), by shape of procursus (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61CFFED28E29C37305F7A1F" box="[745,845,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURES470–475" captionStartId="107.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,301,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[151,1436,301,1907]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURES470–475. Mesabolivar itajai sp. n. (UFMG 21528).470–471. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views.472, 475. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 473–474. Left procursus, prolateral and dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.5 (470– 471), 0.3 (472–475)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202633/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Fig. 471</figureCitation>
; proximally strongly bent towards ventral), and by shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61CFFED2B709CDB310B7AC3" box="[379,537,905,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 476–480" captionStartId="108.[151,264,1459,1481]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,200,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@108.[151,1436,193,1437]" captionTargetPageId="108" captionText="FIGURES 476–480. Mesabolivar itajai sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19197). 476–479. Epigynum, ventral, frontal, posterior, and lateral views.480.Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202635/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Figs 476–479</figureCitation>
; unique membranous scape with terminal pocket).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
